Ogbonnaya Ikokwu, Umuahia The Chief of Staff to the Abia State Governor, Chief Anthony Agbazuere, has warned security agents at the Abia State boundaries against acts likely to endanger the lives of Abia residents. Agbazuere, who gave the warning while addressing journalists at the Government House, Umuahia during the fumigation of the complex by the Ministry of Environment, noted that the state would resist any attempt to endanger the lives of residents by compromising the sit-at-home order to prevent the spread of coronavirus. He added that sanctions would be applied on any person found sabotaging the order. He further advised those distributing the palliatives provided by the state government to be honest as people were complaining of the food items not getting to them. “We are going to reach out to all. Abia residents should be careful, we are praying to God to forgive our sins, COVID-19 is strange, it is devastating. We are amazed but we believe God will protect His people,” he said. While commending the Ministry of Environment for carrying out the fumigation of the Government House and other places, he advised the people to abide by government’s directives and other precautionary measures, observe regular washing of hands, using of sanitisers and also to maintain basic hygiene, saying that COVID-19 was real and that everybody should be prayerful. Copyright PUNCH.
